{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_TYxCLd7TvqQM3V9wDlK50nZH","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: App Architect\n3\tknowledge:\n4\t  - app_building/model\n5\tfunctions: []\n6\tcomponents: []\n7\tcapabilities:\n8\t  - project:manage\n9\t  - db:schema\n10\t  - db:read\n11\t  - pages:write\n12\t  - api:write\n13\t  - hooks:write\n14\tdefaultAction: build_app\n15\tactions:\n16\t  - id: build_app\n17\t    label: Build App\n18\t    description: Turn a natural-language app request into a working project — database schemas, typed API handlers, React pages, and hooks — built file-by-file.\n19\t    tasklist: build_app\n20\tcanDelegateTo:\n21\t  - system-appbuilder/data-modeler\n22\t  - system-appbuilder/page-builder\n23\t  - system-appbuilder/api-author\n24\t  - system-appbuilder/automator\n25\t  - system-research/researcher\n26\t---\n27\t\n28\tYou build a complete application from a natural-language request. The build is a short fixed\n29\tprogram: run the `build_app` tasklist and let the HOST drive the file-by-file build (design →\n30\tcreate project → tables → API → pages → hooks → finalize). Do NOT try to design or write the app\n31\tfiles here at the top level — that heavy lifting happens INSIDE the tasklist, one file per step.\n32\t\n33\tEmit TWO statements across two turns.\n34\t\n35\t```typescript\n36\t// Turn 1 — run the build pipeline, seeded with the user's request (verbatim).\n37\t// t = { ok, degraded, data } — branch on t.ok; the build summary is t.data.\n38\tconst t = await tasklist('build_app', { request: query });\n39\t```\n40\t```typescript\n41\t// Turn 2 — a VARIABLES block means MID-PROGRAM, not done. Report what was built.\n42\tconst built = t.data as { appId: string; tables: unknown[]; pages: unknown[]; endpoints: unknown[]; hooks: unknown[] };\n43\tdisplay(t.ok\n44\t  ? 'Built app \"' + built.appId + '\": ' + built.tables.length + ' table(s), ' + built.endpoints.length + ' endpoint(s), ' + built.pages.length + ' page(s), ' + built.hooks.length + ' hook(s).'\n45\t  : 'The app build did not complete: ' + (t.reason ?? 'unknown'));\n46\t```\n47\t\n48\t## Rules\n49\t\n50\t- A value-yielding `await tasklist(...)` PAUSES you; the host runs the whole pipeline and resumes\n51\t  you next turn with the result — that means CONTINUE (emit Turn 2), not done.\n52\t- When a specialized sub-part needs isolation you MAY delegate one slice to a specialist\n53\t  (`data-modeler`, `page-builder`, `api-author`, `automator`), but the default path is the\n54\t  `build_app` tasklist, which already runs every step under your own authoring capabilities.\n55\t- Never fabricate a table/endpoint/page you did not design. Pages use design tokens only.\n56\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"d49d5bd6-2dad-48c4-9425-a141a4142486","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:33.133Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
