{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_TG9CCMahArG3lMJGTpVPae3r","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: create_project\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  root: string\n6\t  ok: boolean\n7\tdependsOn: [design]\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tCreate the project that every later step writes into. Call `createProject` with the designed\n13\t`appId` and title, then resolve. `createProject` selects the new project as the current authoring\n14\ttarget, so the downstream table/api/page/hook writers land inside it. Emit:\n15\t\n16\tconst c = createProject(design.appId, { title: design.title });\n17\t// c = { ok, appId?, root?, error? }. If c.ok is false, the appId likely collides — read c.error.\n18\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId: c.ok ? (c.appId ?? design.appId) : design.appId, root: c.root ?? \"\", ok: c.ok });\n19\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"272ba92e-2db7-4f7a-870d-27b5942eab5e","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.138Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_p2V2dFTKOQBv456glnNMngZm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  request: string\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\tBuild a complete, working application inside the current project from a natural-language\n7\t`request`, ONE FILE AT A TIME. The pipeline first DESIGNS the app (an appId, tables, endpoints,\n8\tpages, hooks), then creates the project and writes each file with the injected authoring globals\n9\t(`createProject`/`writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`) — the host runs the steps\n10\tin dependency order and fans the per-table / per-endpoint / per-page / per-hook steps out for you,\n11\teach writing exactly one file. Every table/column/relation carries a real description; pages use\n12\t`@lmthing/css` design tokens only.\n13\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"8b8572d0-23d7-4a13-9649-ae3b64c0652a","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.139Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UUuTEsNU0cCl7TTc0pcwbbam","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tYou are the App Architect — an agent that builds a whole working application inside the user's\n2\tproject: a database (JSON table schemas), typed API handlers, React pages, and automation hooks.\n3\tYou design least-privilege: every table, column, and relation carries a real `description`, and\n4\tyou never fabricate a table, column, endpoint name, or file path — you ground every file in the\n5\tdesign you actually produced. Pages use `@lmthing/css` design tokens only (never a raw\n6\thex/rgb/hsl or stock Tailwind color). You build the app file-by-file with the injected authoring\n7\tglobals (`createProject`/`writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`), each a\n8\tsynchronous `{ ok }` call — never prose, always code with `// comment` narration.\n9\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"0ce440e8-9e6b-4035-98b4-da27746e00d4","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.140Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_HL9C7djUSYzsGyYjweup41NW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: design\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  title: string\n6\t  tables: array\n7\t  pages: array\n8\t  endpoints: array\n9\t  hooks: array\n10\tdependsOn: []\n11\trole: general\n12\tfunctions: []\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tDesign the whole app from `request`. This is the THINKING step: reason from the request into a\n16\tconcrete build plan, then resolve it. You have no file tools here — just produce the plan object.\n17\t\n18\tSubstitute REAL values for every `<…>` below (never leave a placeholder in the resolved values).\n19\tDerive a short lowercase-slug `appId` from the request (letters/digits/hyphen, starts with a\n20\tletter). Each endpoint `route` MUST encode its HTTP method last, e.g. `items-list/GET` or\n21\t`items-create/POST`. Each page `route` is `index` (the app root) or a path like `items/[id]`.\n22\t\n23\tconst appId = \"<lowercase-slug derived from the request, e.g. habit-tracker>\";\n24\tconst title = \"<human-readable app title>\";\n25\t// Each table: { name, schema } where schema = { title, description, columns:{...}, relations? }.\n26\t// Every column and relation needs a description; exactly one primaryKey column (uuid).\n27\tconst tables = [\n28\t  { name: \"<table_slug>\", schema: { title: \"<Title>\", description: \"<what it stores>\", columns: { id: { type: \"string\", description: \"unique id\", primaryKey: true, generated: \"uuid\" } } } }\n29\t];\n30\t// Each endpoint: { route: \"<name>/<METHOD>\", purpose }. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n31\tconst endpoints = [\n32\t  { route: \"<name>/GET\", purpose: \"<what this endpoint returns or does>\" }\n33\t];\n34\t// Each page: { route, purpose }. Use \"index\" for the root page.\n35\tconst pages = [\n36\t  { route: \"index\", purpose: \"<what the root page shows>\" }\n37\t];\n38\t// Each hook (often none): { slug, purpose }. Cron or database-triggered automation.\n39\tconst hooks = [];\n40\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId, title, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks });\n41\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"540a2722-2716-449c-b497-18b2e1ac8643","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.141Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UNqv6JrnP2BRrn9HsZITJz8l","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tYou are the Automator — the specialist that writes a project's automation directly into\n2\tthe LIVE project with two synchronous writer globals: `writeProjectHook(slug, src)`\n3\t(`hooks/<slug>.ts`, a CONSUMER — an `event` hook subscribing to a source-qualified event\n4\t`<spaceId>/<name>` or `project/<name>`, or a `cron` hook on a schedule) and\n5\t`writeProjectEvent(name, src)` (`events/<name>.ts`, a PRODUCER — an emitter def). An event\n6\thook fires a `trigger` (`space/agent#action`) OR runs an imperative `handler` whose code\n7\tIS the filter. Database writes are events (`project/db.<table>.<event>`), not a separate\n8\thook type. You ground every hook in a real event, table, and agent action, and never\n9\tfabricate one the installed spaces do not declare.\n10\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"feff74a8-9615-4944-a617-b8fa10534a4b","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.142Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_NsHnnMFBkNk0wxJ539FSbEB6","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Tanzania scenario — round 15 report\n2\t\n3\t## Verdict\n4\t\n5\t**Step 2 failed; not fixed after two fresh verification replays.** Step 1 passed on every replay: all supplied files were read through the document/sheet/vision/audio paths, THING made an offer using real material, and no project state was authored.\n6\t\n7\tThe first replay reproduced the known step-2 failure: `organize_material` executed twice, producing eight overlapping spaces, eleven architect delegates, two appbuilder delegates, and an unbuilt app. The first verification confirmed that the L1 fix removed this re-entry, but exposed a direct-automator completion without any authored project artifacts. The second verification routed app construction through the app architect's action DAG, created exactly four appropriately scoped specialists, and invoked one `app-architect#build_app` delegate; nevertheless the nested build finished before creating a project or authoring a table/page. The app still has `appTables: {}`, `pageCount: 0`, and `built: false`.\n8\t\n9\t## Changes\n10\t\n11\t### L1 — trust a completed workflow envelope\n12\t\n13\t- **File / symbol:** `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md` — accepted supplied-material offer path.\n14\t- **Test:** `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/prompt-contract.test.ts` — `user-thing supplied-material organization`.\n15\t- **Documentation:** `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md` — `user-thing/organize_material`.\n16\t- **Why this rung:** failing evidence showed two `organize_material` yields in the same user turn. After the first workflow had registered spaces and delegated the app build, THING used `inspect()` to independently rederive project state, encountered a recovered error, and restarted the workflow. The error-prone post-workflow verification was a caller decision, not a missing primitive.\n17\t- **General principle:** once an orchestrating workflow returns its envelope, the caller reports that outcome and stops; it does not independently reconstruct partial results or restart completed work.\n18\t- **Result:** verified. In `verify-step-02/step-02.json`, one organizer yielded one specialist and one direct appbuilder delegate. The original duplicate-work failure was removed.\n19\t\n20\t### L2 — use the deterministic app-build action boundary\n21\t\n22\t- **File / symbol:** `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/03-build_app.md`.\n23\t- **Test:** `sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts` — shipped `organize_material` DAG assertions.\n24\t- **Documentation:** `org/docs/system-spaces/README.md` — `user-thing/organize_material`.\n25\t- **Why this rung:** with re-entry gone, the direct `system-appbuilder/automator` delegate returned after a recovered survey-variable typecheck error, but the state contained no tables or pages. A direct broad writer has no deterministic completion boundary. The existing `app-architect#build_app` action owns a host-driven `design → create project → per-file authoring → finalize` tasklist, so selecting that action was the lowest structural correction.\n26\t- **General principle:** a request that must produce a complete multi-step deliverable should go through its fixed action workflow rather than a broad direct writer that can report after an intermediate survey.\n27\t- **Result:** not sufficient. In `verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.json`, the runner recorded exactly four specialist-space delegates and one `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app` delegate. Its full evidence records nested `build_app` tasklist yields, but no `createProject`, table, API, or page writer yields. The final project has no app artifacts.\n28\t\n29\t## Evidence\n30\t\n31\t### Initial failure\n32\t\n33\t`attempt-1/step-02.json`:\n34\t\n35\t- eleven architect delegates and two automator delegates;\n36\t- `spaceCount: 8` with overlapping names including `Cairo Stopover`, `Northern Tanzania Safari`, `Tanzania Safari Tracker`, and duplicate Zanzibar/Arusha variants;\n37\t- populated source rows but `appManifest.built: false`.\n38\t\n39\t`attempt-1/step-02.full.json` records the first `organize_material` yield at lines 43–46 and a second at lines 233–236. Between them, the first run had already registered spaces and delegated the app builder.\n40\t\n41\t### First verification — L1 works, direct writer does not\n42\t\n43\t`verify-step-02/step-02.json`:\n44\t\n45\t- one architect delegate and one `system-appbuilder/automator` delegate;\n46\t- `spaceCount: 1`, but `appTables: {}` and `built: false`.\n47\t\n48\t`verify-step-02/step-02.full.json:138-142` records the direct automator's recovered `Cannot find name 'existingTables'`, `existingPages`, `existingHooks`, and `existingEvents` error while it attempted to return a survey result. No project mutation followed.\n49\t\n50\t### Final verification — L2 action handoff still returns early\n51\t\n52\t`verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.json`:\n53\t\n54\t- four architect delegates, one `system-appbuilder/app-architect/build_app` delegate, and no duplicate organizer invocation;\n55\t- four scopes: `Itinerary Logistics`, `Ngorongoro Crater Safari`, `Trip Costs & Budget`, and `Zanzibar & Stone Town`;\n56\t- no web-search/fetch yields;\n57\t- `appTables: {}`, `pageCount: 0`, `built: false`.\n58\t\n59\t`verify-step-02-rerun-2/step-02.full.json:124-134` records the action delegate and its two nested `build_app` tasklist yields. There are no `createProject`, `writeTableSchema`, `writeApi`, or `writePage` yields anywhere in the trace. The remaining issue is therefore inside the nested action-tasklist handoff or completion path, not supplied-material routing, scope inventory, or the direct-writer choice.\n60\t\n61\t## Validation\n62\t\n63\t- `pnpm --dir sdk/org --filter @lmthing/core test -- src/spaces/prompt-contract.test.ts src/spaces/system-spaces-dag.test.ts` — passed.\n64\t- `pnpm --dir sdk/org --filter @lmthing/cli... build` — passed after each source update.\n65\t- `pnpm docs:check` — passed: 118 documents, 4,556 citations.\n66\t- Prompt-diff literal check found no new scenario-specific terms in `organize_material`; existing Tanzania/Cairo examples elsewhere pre-date this round and were not modified.\n67\t- `git diff --check` — passed.\n68\t\n69\t## Remaining failure / next attribution\n70\t\n71\tDo not restore THING's direct app-building path or the direct automator delegation: both were independently proved unsound. The next invocation should trace why an explicit `app-architect#build_app` action emits an outer tasklist yield and then a completed inner `build_app` yield without executing its declared `design`, `create_project`, per-file, and `finalize` nodes. Start at `sdk/org/libs/core/src/delegate/delegate.ts#runDelegate`, `sdk/org/libs/core/src/eval/yield-router.ts#routeCommonYield`, and `sdk/org/libs/core/src/tasklist/orchestrator.ts#runTasklist`, comparing the action delegate's tasklist envelope/capture behavior with a top-level app-architect invocation. This is now a candidate framework completion/handoff gap, but no L3 change was made because this round did not yet prove which lower-level handoff is missing.\n72\t\n73\tAll changes remain uncommitted for human review.\n74\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"60d9fae8-07b5-4eff-bf69-e0562e3500cc","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:42.143Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
