{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_HaPBrivmksLeMYNEbq1xX5tz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_api\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [design, build_table]\n7\tforEach: design.endpoints\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE typed API handler into the project's `api/`. Your endpoint is in `item` =\n13\t{ route, purpose }, where `route` already encodes the method last (e.g. `items-list/GET`). Write\n14\tthe FULL handler source inline: it must export `name`, `description`, an `Input` interface, an\n15\t`Output` interface, and a default `async (input, ctx) => Output` handler that reads/writes via\n16\t`ctx.db` (`await ctx.db.query/insert/update/remove`). Ground it in the tables you designed. Emit:\n17\t\n18\tconst ep = item;\n19\tconst src = [\n20\t  \"export const name = '\" + ep.route.split('/')[0] + \"';\",\n21\t  \"export const description = '\" + ep.purpose.replace(/'/g, \"\") + \"';\",\n22\t  \"export interface Input {}\",\n23\t  \"export interface Output { items: any[] }\",\n24\t  \"export default async function handler(_input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\",\n25\t  \"  const items = await ctx.db.query('\" + (design.tables[0] ? design.tables[0].name : 'items') + \"');\",\n26\t  \"  return { items };\",\n27\t  \"}\",\n28\t].join(\"\\n\");\n29\tconst w = writeApi(ep.route, src);\n30\t// w = { ok, error? }. Rewrite the source and retry if w.ok is false (e.g. a bad route/method).\n31\tcurrentTask.resolve({ route: ep.route, ok: w.ok });\n32\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"69eda029-13a8-4b83-b0b5-382c6e5cdefc","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:57.741Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_GRLXD1jYdNG9IPCS5IWZvhKf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_table\n3\toutput:\n4\t  name: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [design, create_project]\n7\tforEach: design.tables\n8\toptional: true\n9\trole: general\n10\tfunctions: []\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\tWrite ONE table's schema into the project's `database/`. Your table is in `item` =\n14\t{ name, schema }. Call `writeTableSchema` with the schema the design step produced — it already\n15\tcarries `title`, `description`, `columns` (each with a description; one uuid primary key), and any\n16\t`relations`. Emit:\n17\t\n18\tconst t = item;\n19\tconst w = writeTableSchema(t.name, t.schema);\n20\t// w = { ok, error? }. writeTableSchema validates the schema on write — if w.ok is false, read\n21\t// w.error (a missing description or a bad relation) before resolving honestly.\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({ name: t.name, ok: w.ok });\n23\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"eeeae0e6-642b-42e1-8ab9-eacac9501642","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:57.743Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_HXptsclmdkSBb2sEMC6rJVRV","type":"tool_result","content":"85\t  /** Spaces registered at runtime via registerSpace() — the SAME Map reference the\n86\t   *  parent Session owns, so a registerSpace() inside a fork under this delegate is\n87\t   *  visible to later parent delegate() calls (A1 fix — previously a dead path). */\n88\t  dynamicSpaces?: Map<string, Space>;\n89\t}\n90\t\n91\texport async function runDelegate(opts: RunDelegateOpts): Promise<unknown> {\n92\t  const target = `${opts.packageName}/${opts.agentName}`;\n93\t\n94\t  if (opts.depth >= opts.maxDepth) {\n95\t    throw new Error(\n96\t      `Maximum delegation depth (${opts.maxDepth}) exceeded at target \"${target}\"`,\n97\t    );\n98\t  }\n99\t\n100\t  const { space, agent } = await opts.registry.resolveLazy(target);\n101\t\n102\t  // The delegated agent may declare its own model (frontmatter `model:`), e.g. a\n103\t  // vision agent needing a vision-capable model. Its own turns run on that model;\n104\t  // fall back to the caller's inherited model when unset.\n105\t  const turnModel = agent.model ?? opts.model;\n106\t\n107\t  // Seed registry with this space's npm deps so nested delegates can resolve them\n108\t  for (const [pkgName, depSpace] of Object.entries(space.dependentSpaces)) {\n109\t    opts.registry.addSpace(pkgName, depSpace);\n110\t    opts.registry.addSpace(depSpace.dir, depSpace);\n111\t  }\n112\t\n113\t  // Enforce the delegator's canDelegateTo action restriction, when known. The caller\n114\t  // (globals/delegate.ts's yield handler, via the yield-router) passes the resolved\n115\t  // dependency's `allowedActions` for the target agent; `undefined` means \"not\n116\t  // restricted at the caller layer\" (e.g. the top-level session entry point, or a\n117\t  // dependency-less call) and `[]`/populated arrays gate which actions may run.\n118\t  if (opts.action && opts.allowedActions && !opts.allowedActions.includes(opts.action)) {\n119\t    throw new Error(\n120\t      `Delegate target \"${target}\" does not allow action \"${opts.action}\" — allowed actions: ${opts.allowedActions.length ? opts.allowedActions.join(', ') : '(none)'}`,\n121\t    );\n122\t  }\n123\t\n124\t  const tracer = opts.tracer ?? NULL_TRACER;\n125\t  const delegateLabel = `delegate:${opts.packageName}/${opts.agentName}/${opts.action ?? '(model-driven)'}`;\n126\t  // Mint a delegate scope for full observability; end() in finally below\n127\t  const queryPreview =\n128\t    typeof opts.delegateOpts?.query === 'string'\n129\t      ? opts.delegateOpts.query.slice(0, 500)\n130\t      : undefined;\n131\t  const delegateScope = tracer.child(opts.scope, 'delegate', delegateLabel, {\n132\t    pkg: opts.packageName,\n133\t    agent: opts.agentName,\n134\t    action: opts.action,\n135\t    depth: opts.depth,\n136\t    ...(queryPreview !== undefined ? { query: queryPreview } : {}),\n137\t  });\n138\t\n139\t  // Unified canDelegateTo semantics: the DELEGATED agent's own policy decides\n140\t  // whether `delegate` exists in its VM/DTS/prompt, and (yield-time, below)\n141\t  // which targets its calls may hit. Omitted = unrestricted (back-compat);\n142\t  // [] = none; [\"*\"] = unrestricted; list = hard allowlist (+ \"registered:*\").\n143\t  const delegatePolicy = evaluateDelegatePolicy(agent.canDelegateTo, 'agent');\n144\t  const directDeps = resolveDirectDeps(space, agent.canDelegateTo);\n145\t\n146\t  // The universal `global` toolkit (readFile, grep, remember, …) is injected into every\n147\t  // delegate VM below. Surface it in the system prompt AND the typecheck overlay too —\n148\t  // otherwise an agent that calls a bare global tool (e.g. the memory agent's remember())\n149\t  // fails typecheck with \"Cannot find name\", since it declares no functions of its own.\n150\t  const systemFnSources = systemFunctionSources(opts.systemSpaces ?? []);\n151\t  const knowledgePreloads = await resolvePreloadedKnowledge(space, agent);\n152\t  const systemBlock = buildSystemBlock({ space, agent, directDeps, systemFunctions: systemFnSources, knowledgePreloads, omitAsk: true, omitDelegate: delegatePolicy.mode === 'none' });\n153\t\n154\t  // The delegated agent runs with ITS OWN declared app grants, but project-rooted at\n155\t  // the PARENT's projectRoot (forwarded below) — so a delegated specialist mutates the\n156\t  // current project's app, not the system space it lives in.\n157\t  const capabilities = delegateCapabilities(delegatePolicy.mode !== 'none', agent.capabilities ?? {});\n158\t\n159\t  // action is optional. When provided it must exist; when omitted the agent runs\n160\t  // model-driven and may initiate one of its own actions' tasklists (its # Actions\n161\t  // section is rendered into the system prompt by buildSystemBlock).\n162\t  const actionDef = opts.action ? agent.actions.find((a) => a.id === opts.action) : undefined;\n163\t  if (opts.action && !actionDef) {\n164\t    throw new Error(`Action \"${opts.action}\" not found on agent \"${agent.slug}\"`);\n165\t  }\n166\t\n167\t  const query = opts.delegateOpts?.query ?? '';\n168\t  const context = opts.delegateOpts?.context;\n169\t\n170\t  // Result capture. Tasklists whose result should be auto-captured if the model\n171\t  // forgets to call currentTask.resolve(): the action's own tasklist when an action\n172\t  // was given, or ANY of the agent's action tasklists when delegated model-driven.\n173\t  let capturedResult: unknown = undefined;\n174\t  let resultCaptured = false;\n175\t  const capturableTasklists = actionDef?.tasklist\n176\t    ? new Set<string>([actionDef.tasklist])\n177\t    : new Set<string>(agent.actions.map((a) => a.tasklist).filter(Boolean));\n178\t\n179\t  // Space functions injected into the VM (system functions + agent functions).\n180\t  const agentFunctions = getAgentFunctions(space, agent);\n181\t  const agentFunctionsBundled = getAgentFunctionsBundled(space, agent);\n182\t  const agentComponents = getAgentComponents(space, agent);\n183\t  const systemSpaces = opts.systemSpaces ?? [];\n184\t  const functions = { ...systemFnSources, ...agentFunctions };\n185\t  const functionsBundled = { ...systemFunctionsBundled(systemSpaces), ...agentFunctionsBundled };\n186\t\n187\t  // Shared child-VM bootstrap: query/context seed vars, currentTask capture,\n188\t  // functions, host tools, yielding globals per the capability profile (no ask —\n189\t  // a delegated agent is a programmatic sub-agent that must run autonomously from\n190\t  // its query/context; no registerSpace) and the JSX runtime with this agent's\n191\t  // component stubs. NOTE: no `progress` — the delegate's own turn loop carries\n192\t  // no Budget today (only the forks it spawns do, via budgetLimits below).\n193\t  const vm = await createChildVM({\n194\t    capabilities,\n195\t    renderHost: opts.renderHost,\n196\t    clock: opts.clock,\n197\t    spaceDir: space.dir,\n198\t    projectSpacesDir: opts.projectSpacesDir,\n199\t    projectRoot: opts.projectRoot,\n200\t    projectId: opts.projectId,\n201\t    appGlobals: opts.appGlobals,\n202\t    progress: undefined,\n203\t    functions,\n204\t    functionsBundled,\n205\t    componentNames: [...Object.keys(agentComponents.view), ...Object.keys(agentComponents.form)],\n206\t    onDisplay: (value) => {\n207\t      tracer.write({ ts: Date.now(), type: 'display', context: delegateScope.label, nodeId: delegateScope.nodeId, descriptor: value });\n208\t    },\n209\t    currentTaskResolve: (value) => {\n210\t      capturedResult = value;\n211\t      resultCaptured = true;\n212\t    },\n213\t    // Expose the seed as real VM variables so the agent can pass structured data\n214\t    // straight into its tasklist (`tasklist(action, context)`) — see the seed\n215\t    // declarations in the ambient DTS below.\n216\t    seedVars: { query, context: context ?? {} },\n217\t    onFunctionError: (name, error) => {\n218\t      opts.renderHost.log(`[warn] failed to inject function \"${name}\": ${error}`);\n219\t    },\n220\t  });\n221\t\n222\t  try {\n223\t    const history = new MessageHistory();\n224\t\n225\t    const tasklistHint = actionDef?.tasklist\n226\t      ? `Implement this action by calling \\`const result = await tasklist(\"${actionDef.tasklist}\", { query, ...context })\\` — \\`query\\` (string) and \\`context\\` (object) are in scope as real variables holding the seed data above; the tasklist's input schema needs \\`query\\` INSIDE the seed object, so spread both as shown. The tasklist handles the orchestration. After it resolves, call \\`currentTask.resolve(result)\\`.`\n227\t      : actionDef\n228\t        ? `When complete, call \\`currentTask.resolve(result)\\` with the final result value.`\n229\t        : `Handle this request directly. If one of your actions fits (see \"# Actions\"), run its tasklist with \\`const result = await tasklist(\"<name>\", { query, ...context })\\`. When done, call \\`currentTask.resolve(result)\\` with the final result value.`;\n230\t    const userMessage = [\n231\t      opts.action ? `Run action: ${opts.action}` : `You have been delegated this request — handle it using your available actions/tasklists or directly.`,\n232\t      query ? `Query: ${query}` : '',\n233\t      context ? `Context: ${JSON.stringify(context)}` : '',\n234\t      // File attachments contribute an id-anchored note here telling this agent to\n235\t      // fetch their content via readDocument(id). Image attachments ride as a part.\n236\t      ...(opts.attachmentTexts ?? []),\n237\t      tasklistHint,\n238\t    ]\n239\t      .filter(Boolean)\n240\t      .join('\\n');\n241\t\n242\t    // Attachments (image/file MediaParts) ride on the delegate's user message so a\n243\t    // vision/file agent's model actually receives the image/document. The turn loop\n244\t    // + provider layer already forward `attachments` into the ModelMessage content.\n245\t    history.append({\n246\t      role: 'user',\n247\t      content: userMessage,\n248\t      ...(opts.attachments && opts.attachments.length ? { attachments: opts.attachments } : {}),\n249\t      blockType: 'normal',\n250\t    });\n251\t\n252\t    // Ambient DTS via the shared additive builder: library minus `ask`, this\n253\t    // agent's function/component overlay, the currentTask capture global, and\n254\t    // the query/context seed variables (injected as real VM variables above so\n255\t    // an agent can seed its tasklist with structured data handed down by the\n256\t    // delegator instead of re-serializing it from prose).\n257\t    const overlay = buildOverlay({ ...systemFnSources, ...agentFunctions }, agentComponents);\n258\t    const ambientDts = buildAmbientDts({\n259\t      capabilities,\n260\t      overlay,\n261\t      currentTask: true,\n262\t      projectRoot: !!opts.projectRoot,\n263\t      extraDecls: [`declare const query: string;\\ndeclare const context: Record<string, any>;`],\n264\t    });\n265\t\n266\t    // Runs a child delegate — from this agent's top level OR from one of its tasks' forks —\n267\t    // one level deeper, with the recursion cap enforced by runDelegate's depth/maxDepth.\n268\t    // Spreading opts forwards the inherited parent context (budgetLimits/roleModels/\n269\t    // dynamicSpaces/projectSpacesDir/…) down arbitrary nesting.\n270\t    const runChildDelegate = (\n271\t      packageName: string,\n272\t      agentName: string,\n273\t      action: string | undefined,\n274\t      childOpts: DelegateOpts | undefined,\n275\t      allowedActions: string[] | undefined,\n276\t    ): Promise<unknown> =>\n277\t      runDelegate({\n278\t        ...opts,\n279\t        packageName,\n280\t        agentName,\n281\t        action,\n282\t        allowedActions,\n283\t        delegateOpts: childOpts,\n284\t        scope: delegateScope,\n285\t        depth: opts.depth + 1,\n286\t      });\n287\t\n288\t    const { ForkEngine } = await import('../fork/fork.js');\n289\t    // THE A1 FIX: the delegate-side ForkEngine is built through the same\n290\t    // exhaustively-typed options builder as the session's, so it can no longer\n291\t    // silently drop fields — it now inherits budgetLimits (leaf forks get real\n292\t    // budgets + the near-limit nudge), roleModels (right per-role model),\n293\t    // forkDepth (meaningful nesting accounting) and dynamicSpaces (a fork's\n294\t    // registerSpace() propagates back to the session) from its parent context.\n295\t    const forkEngine = new ForkEngine(forkEngineOptsFrom({\n296\t      maxConcurrentForks: opts.maxConcurrentForks,\n297\t      parentHistory: history.messages,\n298\t      parentSpaceDir: space.dir,\n299\t      parentAgentSlug: agent.slug,\n300\t      parentAgentCharter: agent.charterBody,\n301\t      agentFunctions: functions,\n302\t      agentFunctionsBundled: functionsBundled,\n303\t      renderHost: opts.renderHost,\n304\t      streamFn: opts.streamFn,\n305\t      clock: opts.clock,\n306\t      tracer: opts.tracer,\n307\t      projectSpacesDir: opts.projectSpacesDir,\n308\t      projectRoot: opts.projectRoot,\n309\t      projectId: opts.projectId,\n310\t      // This delegate's forks inherit ITS app grants (role-intersected in forkCapabilities).\n311\t      parentAppCapabilities: capabilities.app,\n312\t      appGlobals: opts.appGlobals,\n313\t      defaultModel: opts.model,\n314\t      budgetLimits: opts.budgetLimits,\n315\t      roleModels: opts.roleModels,\n316\t      // Forks spawned by this delegate nest one level below its delegation depth:\n317\t      // a top-level delegate (depth 0) spawns depth-1 forks (same as session forks);\n318\t      // each nested delegate layer pushes its forks one level deeper.\n319\t      forkDepth: opts.depth + 1,\n320\t      dynamicSpaces: opts.dynamicSpaces,\n321\t      // A task in this agent's tasklist may delegate (gated by its own canDelegateTo); route it\n322\t      // through the same depth-incrementing runner this agent uses for its own delegate() calls.\n323\t      delegateRunner: (packageName, agentName2, action, childOpts, allowedActions) =>\n324\t        runChildDelegate(packageName, agentName2, action, childOpts as DelegateOpts | undefined, allowedActions),\n325\t      // Forks under this delegate may read attachments too — thread the resolver.\n326\t      documentResolver: opts.documentResolver,\n327\t    }));\n328\t\n329\t    try {\n330\t      await runTurnLoop({\n331\t        vm,\n332\t        history,\n333\t        systemBlock,\n334\t        ambientDts,\n335\t        renderHost: opts.renderHost,\n336\t        streamFn: opts.streamFn,\n337\t        processYield: async (req) => {\n338\t          // sleep / fork / tasklist / delegate share the central router. The two\n339\t          // delegate-specific behaviours are passed as hooks: auto-capture of the\n340\t          // action's tasklist result, and depth-incremented recursion.\n341\t          const routed = await routeCommonYield(req, {\n342\t            space,\n343\t            clock: opts.clock,\n344\t            tracer: opts.tracer,\n345\t            scope: delegateScope,\n346\t            apiCallResolver: opts.appGlobals?.apiCall,\n347\t            apiCallAllow: capabilities.app['api:call']?.allow,\n348\t            connectionResolver: opts.appGlobals?.callConnection,\n349\t            documentResolver: opts.documentResolver,\n350\t            // Store search/inspect + manual emits work in delegates (system-store\n351\t            // runs AS a delegate of THING); consent-marked kinds (installSpace)\n352\t            // still FAIL CLOSED here — no requestConsent is wired (delegates are\n353\t            // headless), so the router's consent gate refuses before install.\n354\t            storeResolver: opts.appGlobals?.store,\n355\t            emitEventResolver: opts.appGlobals?.emitEvent,\n356\t            // installSpace live-registers into the session-shared map (visible to\n357\t            // the parent's later delegate()) — same reference forks receive.\n358\t            dynamicSpaces: opts.dynamicSpaces,\n359\t            getForkEngine: () => forkEngine,\n360\t            // `result` is the tasklist's TaskEnvelope ({ ok, degraded, data, … })\n361\t            // since Phase 3 — captured and returned UNTOUCHED, so the delegator\n362\t            // sees the same envelope contract as a direct tasklist() caller.\n363\t            onTasklistResult: (name, result) => {\n364\t              if (capturableTasklists.has(name) && !resultCaptured) {\n365\t                capturedResult = result;\n366\t                resultCaptured = true;\n367\t              }\n368\t            },\n369\t            runDelegate: (packageName, agentName, action, delegateOpts2) => {\n370\t              // Yield-time canDelegateTo gate (unified semantics): this agent's\n371\t              // policy decides whether the target is callable at all — an\n372\t              // out-of-list target throws an actionable, retryable error naming\n373\t              // the allowed targets. `registered:*` consults the session-shared\n374\t              // dynamicSpaces map at call time. On an allowlist match, the\n375\t              // entries' `#action` suffixes narrow the allowed actions (the same\n376\t              // enforcement the old directDeps lookup fed into runDelegate).\n377\t              const allow = isDelegateAllowed(delegatePolicy, packageName, agentName, opts.dynamicSpaces);\n378\t              if (!allow.allowed) {\n379\t                throw new Error(formatDelegateDenial(delegatePolicy, packageName, agentName, 'agent'));\n380\t              }\n381\t              return runChildDelegate(packageName, agentName, action, delegateOpts2, allow.allowedActions);\n382\t            },\n383\t          });\n384\t          return routed.handled ? routed.value : undefined;\n385\t        },\n386\t        maxRetries: 3,\n387\t        tracer: tracer,\n388\t        traceContext: delegateLabel,\n389\t        scope: delegateScope,\n390\t        model: turnModel,\n391\t      });\n392\t      // GUARANTEE (mirrors fork.ts): a delegate whose model finished without calling\n393\t      // currentTask.resolve() — and without running a capturable tasklist — must not\n394\t      // hand `undefined` back to the delegator. The live E4 failure: the engineer did"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"71a8f40f-11cd-4ffe-ab9d-94d75b2025b2","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:29:57.744Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace organizer app routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_7ydX4mqgdMgjsM4ks8BUiDr5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_page\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [design, build_api]\n7\tforEach: design.pages\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE React page into the project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` = { route, purpose }\n13\t(`index` is the app root; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route). Write the FULL `.tsx` source inline.\n14\tImport data hooks from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n15\tnever `fetch` a raw URL — and read from the endpoints you built. STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN\n16\tTOKENS ONLY: use classes like `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`, `border-border` —\n17\tnever a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color (`gray-500`, `blue-600`). Emit:\n18\t\n19\tconst pg = item;\n20\tconst ep = design.endpoints[0] ? design.endpoints[0].route.split('/')[0] : 'items-list';\n21\tconst src = [\n22\t  \"import { useApi } from '@app/runtime';\",\n23\t  \"\",\n24\t  \"export default function Page() {\",\n25\t  \"  const { data, isLoading } = useApi<{ items: { id: string; title: string }[] }>('\" + ep + \"');\",\n26\t  \"  if (isLoading) return <p className=\\\"text-muted p-4\\\">Loading…</p>;\",\n27\t  \"  return (\",\n28\t  \"    <ul className=\\\"divide-y divide-border\\\">\",\n29\t  \"      {(data?.items ?? []).map((it) => (\",\n30\t  \"        <li key={it.id} className=\\\"p-3 text-foreground\\\">{it.title}</li>\",\n31\t  \"      ))}\",\n32\t  \"    </ul>\",\n33\t  \"  );\",\n34\t  \"}\",\n35\t].join(\"\\n\");\n36\tconst w = writePage(pg.route, src);\n37\t// w = { ok, error? }. Rewrite and retry if w.ok is false.\n38\tcurrentTask.resolve({ route: pg.route, ok: w.ok });\n39\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_uKyNHS8CyEqodhYQflFPJAwN","session_id":"08b44427-7432-4e2d-a9c3-d9296f1761a5","uuid":"0fcf7d75-c07c-4d47-908e-2